The paper deals with indexing text for efficient querying, which is a core topic in computer science. The use case of aligning sequencing data to large genomes suggests a connection to bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The paper also mentions the space complexity of the index, which is a common concern in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of wildcard positions in the text suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB).
